lse, "description": "Area: documentation for any part of the project, including the compiler, standard library, and tools"}, {"id": 2238476604, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMjM4NDc2NjA0", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-fmt", "name": "A-fmt", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: std::fmt"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-09-15T02:28:21Z", "updated_at": "2020-10-09T00:29:37Z", "closed_at": "2020-10-09T00:29:37Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The [docs for `std::fmt::Write`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/fmt/trait.Write.html) discourage using it outside of the standard library:\r\n\r\n> [\u2026] This is similar to the standard library's io::Write trait, but it is only intended for use in libcore.\r\n>\r\n> This trait should generally not be implemented by consumers of the standard library. The `write!` macro accepts an instance of `io::Write`, and the `io::Write` trait is favored over implementing this trait.\r\n\r\nYet it is relatively often that one needs a trait for writing Unicode to a stream. For example, `pulldown-cmark` has a trait very similar to this one called [`StrWrite`](https://docs.rs/pulldown-cmark/0.8.0/pulldown_cmark/escape/trait.StrWrite.html).\r\n\r\nWhen I [asked in Zulip](https://rust-lang.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/122651-general/topic/equivalent.20of.20.60io.3A.3AWrite.60.20that's.20string-oriented.3F), nobody seemed to know why that comment is there.\r\n\r\nIt would be good to have a standard that every library can use for this.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n@rustbot modify labels: A-fmt T-libs T-doc", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_url": "https://a